subhead: Long overlooked, the question of military mobility has returned to the forefront of Western priorities in response to the Russian threat. title: Sinner triumphs over great rival Alcaraz at ATP Finals
subhead: Jannik Sinner, who beat Carlos Alcaraz in straight sets, 7-6 (7/4), 7-5, at the ATP Finals on Sunday, has now won 31 consecutive matches on indoor hard courts. Praising the 'brilliant atmosphere' in Turin amid loud cheers, the Italian compared the fan energy to a football match:  'I'm really happy to have given something positive to all of you.'

subhead: An exhibition brings together approximately 150 works that bear witness to a practice born in ancient China to preserve imprints of relics from the past.

title: Sudan: Humanitarian crisis from Darfur war spills over into Chad
subhead: For more than 20 years, N'Djamena has endured the consequences of the Sudanese conflict, hosting over one million refugees. Chad has also acted as a backer of armed groups when it suits its interests, risking internal destabilization.

title: Designer Pieter Mulier writes a new chapter in Alaïa's history
subhead: After four years as creative director of the couturehouse founded by Azzedine Alaïa, the Belgian designer has just won the International Designer of the Year award at the CFDA Awards in New York. A few months ago, he moved into a modern building in the 11th arrondissement, ushering the brand into a new era.
